                        <a class="story-card__series" href="https://www.propublica.org/series/post-roe-america">Post-Roe America</a>
        
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/idaho-banned-abortion-support-pregnancies-families">
                                    Idaho Banned Abortion. Then It Turned Down Supports for Pregnancies and Births.
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Since the overturn of Roe v. Wade, the state’s GOP-led Legislature has disbanded a maternal mortality committee, failed to expand postpartum Medicaid coverage and turned down federal grants for child care.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/audrey-dutton">Audrey Dutton</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-10-03EDT06:00">Oct. 3, 6 a.m. EDT</time>
        </p>

